= Asciidoctor cheatsheet

Hello, here are examples of the most common structures used
in adoc. Feel free to copy them and use for your benefit.

= Basic formatting
Insert desired text between formatting characters.
This is how you write *bold*. *Whole bold sentence.* +
This is how you write _italics_. _Whole italics sentence._ +
This is how you write `monospace`. `Whole monospace sentence.` +
This is how you write #highlighted#. #Whole highlighted sentence.#

= Using links
Use whole link as EXAMPLE. https://google.com/[EXAMPLE].

= Titles

= Document Title (Level 0)

== Level 1 Section Title

=== Level 2 Section Title

==== Level 3 Section Title

===== Level 4 Section Title

====== Level 5 Section Title

== Another Level 1 Section Title

:sectnums!:

== Unnumbered Section
=== Unnumbered Section

:sectnums:

[[section-one]]
== Section One



[[name-of-reference]]
= References

[[paragraph-reference]] Put this before desired referenced place. You use reference this way <<section-one>> <<paragraph-reference, Text shown on this place>>


= Lists

. first itme of list
. second item of list
. third, multiline item

you see, this is broken, but it is okay, look at the example below

. multiline item
+
--
// use this if you want to have something independent included in the list works
//with all types(description, ordered, unordered), no need for pluses and almost
//unbreakable
indented, not broken

I can even have a sublist here:

. darling
. cheatsheet
. icecream

or an example
----
example
----

Those two dashes marked segment can be inserted to any list
--
. fourth item of list


.Ordered list
. Number of dots equals level of indentation in a list
. Second item of a list
.. 2.1 item of a list
.. 2.2 item of a list
... 2.2.1 item of a list
. Third item of a list


.Unordered list

* Edgar Allen Poe
* Sheri S. Tepper
** Sheri S. Tepper
*** Bill Bryson
+
Indented line without a bullet.
* Bill Bryson

.Unordered list
- Edgar Allen Poe
- Sheri S. Tepper
- Bill Bryson

.Description list
Dairy::
* Milk
* Eggs
Bakery::
* Bread
Produce::
* Bananas

.Nesting an unordered list inside of an ordered list:

. Linux
* Fedora
* Ubuntu
* Slackware
. BSD
* FreeBSD
* NetBSD

//pluses are also a solution for inserting blocks of something into lists but
//it is easy to mistype something and break it

