= Admonitions

//use name and : for single line admonitions and name in brackets fot mulitiline ones
TIP: Single line or one paragraph content.


[NOTE]
Also works for single line texts.

[IMPORTANT]
====
Use four of these -> =  at the beginning and the end of what you want to have written
in the admonition and between them pretend that it is plain space and use

.Lists
. Something
. Something
====

[WARNING]
====
.Images
image::https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/3/35/Tux.svg[Tux,250,350]
====

[CAUTION]
====
Or even tables

[cols="h,m"]

|===

| Cell in column 1, row 1 | Cell in column 2, row 1

| Cell in column 1, row 2 | Cell in column 2, row 2

|===

====


= Including files

Use relative path to another file

include::folder/filename.adoc[]

= Including images
On separate line before image put + symbol, after image tag relative path in
assets to desired image, you can also set
width and align, but it is not necessary.
+
image::folder-path/imagename.png[width=429, align="center"]

= Including custom web content (GMap, albums, ...)

Paste link into src property of iframe

