= Header file you should include in every project

// Include headers in all files to support Atom's Asciidoc Preview plugin.
ifndef::header[]
:header:

:toc: left
//determines on which side is the table of contents
:doctype: book
//Doctype can be article, book or manpage
:sectlinks:
//When this document attribute is set, the section titles become self-links.
//This enables a reader to bookmark the section.
:sectanchors:
//When this document attribute is set, a section icon anchor appears in front
//of the section title.
:sectnums:
//:sectnums: - sections are numbered; :sectnums!: - sections are not numbered
//you can change it inside a document and will be applied to the rest from the
//point where you change it or until you change it to the other one
:icons: font
//This must be included to have Admonitions icons available
:experimental:
// Enables some macros
:source-highlighter: highlightjs
//Enabling the syntax highlighter

:highlightjsdir: assets/highlight
:stem:
:linkattrs:
:toclevels: 3
include::roles.adoc[]
include::urls.adoc[]
:t: pass:[<span style="white-space:nowrap">&thinsp;</span>]
:commandkey: &#8984;
endif::header[]

This is standard we use in our handbooks, feel free to modify it so it will suit you.

[WARNING]
===
Include all other adoc files

....
 include::roles.adoc[]
 include::urls.adoc[]
 ...
....

Include header at the top of each document inside other parts as a relative file path, if on the same level omit ../
....
 include::../header.adoc[]
....
===
